-- Simple
    Java is simple, clean and easy to understand
    You don't need to remove unreferenced objects
        because Java has Automatic Garbage Collection.

-- Object-Oriented
    Anything in Java is object
    The basic concepts of Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)
        Object
        Class
        Inheritance
        Polymorphism
        Abstraction
        Encapsulation

-- Portable
    Java's portability allows developers to <write code once and run it anywhere> with JVM

-- Platform Independent
    Java is a software-based platform. Java code will be compiled and converted into bytecode by compiler
    Bytecode is platform-independent because it can run various platforms.

-- Secured
    Java is secure because
        No explicit pointers
        Java programs run inside a virtual machine sandbox

-- Robust
    Robust is strong
    It employs strong memory management